transcripts: We're comparing the kitchenaid artisan 5-quart with the newly-designed breville 5-quart stand mixer . It's the old versus teh new in a head-to-head battle. The challenge, speed control and timer. Our design is all about maximamizing the experience of the people using it . You want your controller knobs to be easily accessible and also want to let an appliance do its job without worrying about it . Noticed that the kitchen it has this go on forever and on the outside there's no countdown timer or auto shut off . So that means you have to always be around it monitor your mix . The breville controls are very easy and intuitive ergonomically positioned right on top using led lights fro ease of use. There are also handy guides inside them when you're in the kitchen . The countdown timer lets you do other tasks while the breville stand mixer blends perfectly. The breville stand mixer see it for yourself; it's built for baking.
